textRun.content: This is a club/EC information page that execs or supervisors of their respective clubs/ECs at KSS should fill out, which will automatically update on
Please only change or add stuff in the tables, and follow the instructions closely! Leave sections blank if you don’t have anything to write.
Ignore this section unless you absolutely know what you are doing! Editing it may result in the rest of your webpage not updating! This is meant only for KSS Directory admins.
Basic information about your club/EC that you can edit yourself.
Let students know what your club/EC is all about! Keep it concise; don’t add meeting times/dates, supervisors, etc.

The Student Council (SC) plays a vital role in providing a student voice within Kingston Secondary School. Students are able to share their ideas on issues within the school as well as provide leadership to initiatives that help make it safer, education-focused and fun. Testing crap 2 3 4 5 6 7 1
Answer with either “yes” or “no”. This does not mean your club/EC will be removed from the KSS Directory database.

List one supervisor name per cell in this table. 2 slots are given, but you are free to leave any blank. If you don’t have a supervisor, leave this section blank. If you have more supervisors, insert another row at the bottom of the table.

Information on when your club/EC meets each week that you can edit yourself. Do not add one-off events here, as they show up as recurring on the website. 3 slots are given, but you are free to leave any blank. You can also insert new rows if you have more than 3 meetings. The columns with the * must be filled out if you wish for the meeting time to show up on your website.
Short info about the meeting, e.g. “Tutoring session”
Only include the day of the week here, e.g. “Monday”
Write using AM/PM clock, e.g. “2:45 PM”
Write using AM/PM clock, e.g. “3:30 PM”

Add any external links that you may have for your club/EC, such as Instagram pages or Google Forms. 3 slots are given, but you are free to leave any blank. You can also insert new rows if you have more than 3 links.
Make sure to add as URL, e
If your club/EC has a logo that you want to display on your Club Directory page, paste it in the following Table. If you don’t have one, you can leave this area blank.
If you want to display an image as a banner on your Club Directory page, paste it in the following table. If you don’t have one, you can leave this area blank.

A list of your Club/EC’s current executive members. If you don’t have any (or this is not applicable for your club/EC) then you can leave this section blank. 5 slots are given, but you are free to leave any blank. You can also insert new rows if you have more than 5 execs.
The name of your club’s executive members, e.g. “John Doe”
The title of their executive position, e.g. “Marketing”
Display any events pertaining to your club/EC on your webpage
You can have up to 3 concurrent events. If you require more, please ask a KSS Directory maintainer to help you.
The table for all information pertaining to your first event. If any of the required fields are empty or invalid, then the event will not be displayed on the website.
Determines if the event will show up on the website. Type in “yes” or “no”
